  "event_preview": "Bristol Motor Speedway is a 0.533-mile (0.858 km) concrete oval in Bristol, Tennessee, with banking that varies from 24 to 28 degrees in the turns. Opened in 1961, it is known as the Last Great Colosseum - a stadium-style short track with seating for 146,000 and the only venue on the NASCAR calendar still running two pit road lanes. The Tennessee Army National Guard 250 is the sixth race of the 2026 NASCAR Craftsman Truck Series season and the final leg of the Triple Truck Challenge, which carries a $500,000 bonus for sweeping all three events. The race runs 250 laps (133.25 miles) on the all-concrete surface, with stage breaks at laps 65 and 130. The all-time Truck Series qualifying lap record at Bristol belongs to Connor Zilisch, who turned a 15.325-second lap (125.207 mph) in September 2024 qualifying - his first ever trip to the half-mile. The fastest lap in race conditions belongs to Kyle Larson, who turned a 15.38-second effort in the 2025 spring race en route to a second-place finish behind Chandler Smith."
}
